1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,959
2.

2
00:00:01,229 --> 00:00:05,279
Be a comfortable person, so there is no strain in being with you.

3
00:00:05,469 --> 00:00:08,320
Be an old-shoe kind of individual.

4
00:00:08,320 --> 00:00:09,600
3.

5
00:00:09,870 --> 00:00:15,120
Acquire the quality of relaxed, easy-going, so that things do not ruffle you.

6
00:00:15,120 --> 00:00:16,399
4.

7
00:00:16,750 --> 00:00:18,560
Don't be egotistical.

8
00:00:18,669 --> 00:00:21,600
Guard against the impression that you know it all.

9
00:00:21,600 --> 00:00:22,800
5.

10
00:00:23,149 --> 00:00:29,920
Cultivate the quality of being interesting, so people will get something of value from their association with you.

11
00:00:29,920 --> 00:00:31,279
6.

12
00:00:31,630 --> 00:00:38,639
Study to get the scratchy elements out of your personality, even those of which you may be unconscious.

13
00:00:38,639 --> 00:00:40,079
7.

14
00:00:40,430 --> 00:00:47,440
Sincerely attempt to heal, on an honest basis, every misunderstanding you have had or now have.

15
00:00:47,550 --> 00:00:49,600
Drain off your grievances.

16
00:00:50,190 --> 00:00:50,880
8.

17
00:00:51,149 --> 00:00:55,519
Practice liking people until you learn to do so genuinely.

18
00:00:56,109 --> 00:00:56,800
9.

19
00:00:57,070 --> 00:01:06,160
Never miss an opportunity to say a word of congratulation upon anyone's achievement or express sympathy in sorrow or disappointment.

20
00:01:06,829 --> 00:01:07,440
10.

21
00:01:07,789 --> 00:01:13,120
Give spiritual strength to people, and they will give genuine affection to you.

22
00:01:14,110 --> 00:01:22,240
Living these ten simple but tremendously powerful like-people rules makes President Johnson easier to vote for,

23
00:01:22,269 --> 00:01:24,399
easier to support in Congress.

24
00:01:24,589 --> 00:01:29,440
Living these ten rules makes President Johnson easier to lift.

25
00:01:29,950 --> 00:01:31,920
Listen to these rules again.

26
00:01:32,110 --> 00:01:35,440
Notice that there's no get-even philosophy here.

27
00:01:35,630 --> 00:01:39,920
There's no let-the-other-fellow-come-to-me to patch up differences.

28
00:01:40,110 --> 00:01:43,600
There's no I-know-it-all-other-people-are-stupid.

29
00:01:44,110 --> 00:01:51,440
Big people, those on top in industry, the arts, sciences, and politics, are human, warm.

30
00:01:51,630 --> 00:01:54,079
They specialize in being likable.

31
00:01:54,669 --> 00:01:57,040
But don't try to buy friendship.

32
00:01:57,070 --> 00:01:58,560
It's not for sale.

33
00:01:59,070 --> 00:02:04,800
Giving gifts is a wonderful practice if the gift is backed up with genuine sincerity,

34
00:02:04,909 --> 00:02:09,040
a liking to give, and liking for the person to whom it is given.

35
00:02:09,229 --> 00:02:16,079
But without real sincerity, the gift is often regarded as nothing more than a payoff or a bribe.

36
00:02:17,149 --> 00:02:24,800
Last year, just a few days before Christmas, I was in the office of the president of a medium-sized trucking firm.

